{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n      \n        Admin Portal Owns Hiatus Schedule\n        Flow: Admin sets hiatus dates in portal → Portal pauses in Kajabi → Portal auto-resumes when date arrives\n\n        \n          How it works:\n          \n            Admin Portal stores: hiatus_start_date, hiatus_end_date\n            On start date: Portal calls Kajabi API to pause subscription\n            On end date: Portal calls Kajabi API to resume subscription\n            Portal handles all Slack channel removals/re-invites\n          \n        \n\n        \n          \n            Pros:\n            \n              Portal is single source of truth for hiatus\n              Can track hiatus history easily\n              Can see upcoming hiatus end dates\n              Auto-resume logic lives in one place\n            \n          \n          \n            Cons:\n            \n              Need scheduled job for auto-resume\n              If member manually resumes in Kajabi, creates conflict\n              Portal must reconcile external changes","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776389368139}
